Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈkom.pe.toː/, [ˈkɔm.pɛ.t̪oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈkom.pe.to/, [ˈkɔm.pɛ.t̪ɔ]

Etymology 1[edit]

From con- +‎ petō.

Verb[edit]

competō (present infinitive competere, perfect active competīvī or competiī, supine competītum); third conjugation

  1. come together, meet
  2. agree, coincide in point of time
  3. be equal to, be capable of
